<br>
I know it is a dream, and believe me, I do know how difficult halfway decent AI is, but it would be the single largest improvement in the game.<br>
<br>
As a GM I would never let players get away with the tactics they do.  Divide and conquer, no wonder the monsters have to be so tough.  I would make pulling more difficult, and make facing groups of spawns together the norm, rather than exception.<br>
<br>
With genetic algorithms, it might even be possible to have mob AIs evolve over time in response to player tactics.<br>
<br>
As it is, the tactics in the game are highly artificial, and do not reflect what is done with pen-and-paper or miniatures games.<br>
<br>
Over a quarter century as a dungeon master,<br>
