<br>
Assuming an equal amount of playing time, the player who can play for 4 consecutive hours in a day has a major advantage over people who might be able to play for 4-1 hour sessions in a day. Some of this is social engineering, some is directly game related. It would be nice to see things shifted a bit in this regard.<br>
<br>
Smarter AI would be nice, even if they just randomized some of the existing AI (cause uber mobs to kill clerics randomly). So much of the mid-high end game is repeating the same tactics over and over again. Naturally if the AI were scrambled or improved, many mobs would need to be weakened a bit.<br>
<br>
Rare mobs, that drop rare loot aren't a good thing.<br>
<br>
Not to hijack the thread too much, but much of this discussion could be directed towards EQ II. As its really too late to make tons of changes to the EQ I game.<br>
<br>
Where will EQ II Begin in terms of all of the subtle advances EQ I has experienced through all of the expansions? Will we go back to having to wait around for boats? Or will portals be the way to go? <br>
<br>
Personally, I'm hoping for gnomish hot air balloons.....  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
