<br>
This is my number one.  There was a lot of lore in the older days, yet slowly it has become more a level/equipment/I killed xxx type of game.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think they should do this:<br>
<br>
1.  Go through all the old busted quests and either remove the NPC text (if no longer relevent), or verify they do in fact work and people haven't solved them (this probably means verify the drop tables).<br>
<br>
2.  Fill in some of the lore.  A GM used to play King Thex and whats her name Mistmore didn't they?  Bring them back.<br>
<br>
3.  Faction has become a joke.  Luclin and PoP pretty well ignore old faction.  Iksar Necro aint that hard to play, just go to the moon, do a couple of faction quests, and you are on the same standing as a Mith Mar cleric.  This was a massive mistake I feel, as the roleplay aspect has dropped off more.<br>
<br>
4.  See all those very obvious zone boundries that go nowhere  (Oasis of Marr valley, Akanon, SolA, etc, etc)?  Fill them in.  We don't need a zone like JP with its funky click here to zone portals (thus destroying any concept of geographic connection) when there are very valid places to place new zones.)<br>
<br>
5. (some) Items should decay.  But there is no way I could see how you could add this to the game now without massive problems and upheavel in the economy.  Hopefully EQII builds this in.  <br>
<br>
6.  The game should be renamed Everquest to Evercamp.<br>
<br>
<br>
But hey, this is an aging game and one of the first.  Hindsight is wonderful.  It's still a cool game that soaks up way too much time of mine.<br>
