<br>
2. Make other sources of XP viable. Making the only way to gain XP is to kill random monsters get kinda boring. Quests and other events could be an alternative. (In AO you can gain XP for sucessfully disarming a trap, or unlocking a door or chest. Albeit a small amount, it adds up over time.)<br>
<br>
3. Faction. It use to be a big deal in the old world, but nowadays its a moot point past Velious.<br>
<br>
4. Mob AI, mainly in big encounters. Have an encounter, but set it up 5 different ways, and anytime the encounter is set into motion, a random form of the encoutner happens. <br>
<br>
5. Not enough low / mid - boss encounters. The only ones I can think of is Ambassador D'vin, Mayong Mistmoore (me thinks I gurked up his name.) and Najena ... wow all Dark Elves. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> : <br>
